The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 11 March is 40,707 (4,711.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 06 March, there were 303 new confirmed cases (35.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 27 February, there were 522 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 42% (219 fewer cases).
